<p>In my student days, there was a popular book that compared the â€œaffluentâ€ with the â€œnon-affluentâ€, and sorted everything into categories called â€œloadedâ€ and â€œbroke.â€ It was the bubble era, and the aim of the book was probably to get a laugh by saying â€œThey call us wealthy, but our lifestyleâ€™s practically in the trash can!â€</p>
