<p><code>Y</code>: Iâ€™ve been privileged to work on three King Records shows: <em>Neon Genesis Evangelion</em>, <em>Martian Successor Nadesico</em>, and <em>Revolutionary Girl Utena</em>. Out of the three directors of those shows, Mr.Â Ikuhara is the closest to me in age, so he was easy for me to understand. In my mind, itâ€™s easy to work with someone who grew up in the same age I did, and itâ€™s more exciting. Because the anime and dramas that we watched as kids are the same, and I can see those elements popping up. So I ask him about it, and we both get pumped up talking about it: â€œI used to watch that one! Yeah, and this one!â€</p>
